P/HARCOURT  – A Planned Stakeholders Summit to discuss Protection of Nigeria’s Critical Infrastructure and Assets has been scheduled for July 25- 26, 2022 in Port Harcourt, Rivers State Capital. Dr. Chiakor Alfred, representative of Ashcraft Centre, while addressing Journalists in Port Harcourt at the weekend, said Ashcraft Centre for Social Science and research in collaboration with the Federal Ministries of Petroleum Resources, Transportation, Communication, Digital Economy and Power has planned to hold the South-South Zonal Stakeholders Summit with the Theme, “Domesticating Stakeholders Statutory Responsibilities in Protecting Nigeria Critical Infrastructures and Assets “ which shall provide ample opportunity to domesticate the advocacy campaign on serious critical issues among key stakeholders in attendance as a follow-up on the successful submit earlier held in February at the Transcorp Hilton Hotel in Abuja. Dr. Alfred stated that the last two decades have demonstrated clearly that the nature of threat to Nigeria security has changed significantly; stressing out that the country now faces more security threats such as Systematic vandalisation, degradation and destruction of Nigeria critical national infrastructures and business assets. Dr. Alfred, who is the chief Strategic planner and Innovator at Ashcraft Centre, said that: “the South-South zonal stakeholders summit is therefore, a private, public sector partnership that aims to preserve and protect Nigeria critical national infrastructures and assets”.